Urinary amylase activity and debit as indices of the functional status of the pancreas and gallbladder. The functional state was studied of the pancreas and gallbladder by calculation of the activity and yield of uroamylase in 96 persons. Data are compared that were obtained on the basis of this method. There was a clear correlation with results obtained during cholecystography. This simple and precise method may be recommended for wide practical use.